cmap

Work Sans Thin Regular (WorkSans-Thin.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Work Sans' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Thin' = NID 1 'Work Sans Thin'.

Work Sans Thin Italic (WorkSans-ThinItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Work Sans' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Thin Italic' = NID 1 'Work Sans Thin' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

Work Sans ExtraLight Regular (WorkSans-ExtraLight.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'WorkSans-ExtraLight', Everything looks good.

Pass

Work Sans ExtraLight Italic (WorkSans-ExtraLightItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'WorkSans-ExtraLightItalic', Everything looks good.

Pass

Work Sans ExtraLight Italic (WorkSans-ExtraLightItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Work Sans' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraLight Italic' = NID 1 'Work Sans ExtraLight' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '

NID 6 is 'WorkSans-Light', Everything looks good.

Work Sans Light Regular (WorkSans-Light.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Work Sans' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Light' = NID 1 'Work Sans Light'.

Work Sans Light Italic (WorkSans-LightItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'WorkSans-LightItalic', Everything looks good.

Work Sans Light Italic (WorkSans-LightItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Work Sans' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Light Italic' = NID 1 'Work Sans Light' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Work Sans Italic (WorkSans-Italic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'WorkSans-Italic', Everything looks good.

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'WorkSans-Medium', Everything looks good.

Work Sans Medium Regular (WorkSans-Medium.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Work Sans' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium' = NID 1 'Work Sans Medium'.

Pass

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Work Sans' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium Italic' = NID 1 'Work Sans Medium' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Work Sans SemiBold Regular (WorkSans-SemiBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'WorkSans-SemiBold', Everything looks good.

Pass

Work Sans SemiBold Italic (WorkSans-SemiBoldItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'WorkSans-SemiBoldItalic', Everything looks good.

Work Sans SemiBold Italic (WorkSans-SemiBoldItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Work Sans' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiBold Italic' = NID 1 'Work Sans SemiBold' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

Work Sans Bold (WorkSans-Bold.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'WorkSans-Bold', Everything looks good.

Pass

Work Sans Bold Italic (WorkSans-BoldItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'WorkSans-BoldItalic', Everything looks good.

Work Sans ExtraBold Regular (WorkSans-ExtraBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Work Sans' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraBold' = NID 1 'Work Sans ExtraBold'.

Pass

Work Sans ExtraBold Italic (WorkSans-ExtraBoldItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'WorkSans-ExtraBoldItalic', Everything looks good.

Work Sans ExtraBold Italic (WorkSans-ExtraBoldItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Work Sans' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraBold Italic' = NID 1 'Work Sans ExtraBold' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

Work Sans Black Regular (WorkSans-Black.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'WorkSans-Black', Everything looks good.

Work Sans Black Regular (WorkSans-Black.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Work Sans' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Black' = NID 1 'Work Sans Black'.

Work Sans Black Italic (WorkSans-BlackItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'WorkSans-BlackItalic', Everything looks good.

Work Sans Black Italic (WorkSans-BlackItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Work Sans' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Black Italic' = NID 1 'Work Sans Black' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.
